Chikwe Ihekweazu, Director-General of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), has been quarantined for 14 days. Osagie Ehanire, Minister of Health, announced this on Tuesday, when he met with the senate. Ehanire, while updating the senate on the activities of his ministry, said Ohanire has been quarantined in its activities to curb the spread of coronavirus in the country According to him, Ihekweazu was quarantined because he just returned from China. Nigeria on Thursday confirmed its index case of COVID-19 after an Italian man tested positive. Meanwhile, the House of Representatives on Tuesday closed its legislative activities for two weeks over Coronavirus scare. The resolution was reached following the adoption of a motion by Unyime Idem. Entitled “emergency response to the dreaded coronavirus.”